# CURSOR RULES — FOLDERA

## Read Before Every Session
- AGENTS.md (execution contract)
- CLAUDE.md (operational source of truth)  
- LESSONS_LEARNED.md (permanent rules)
- CURRENT_STATE.md (what layer we're on)

## Stack
- Next.js 14 App Router
- Supabase (RLS enabled, service_role for backend)
- Claude API (Anthropic, NOT OpenAI)
- Tailwind CSS, Lucide React icons
- Dark mode default: bg-slate-950, text-slate-100

## Absolute Rules
- Push directly to main. Never create branches.
- npm run build must pass before every commit.
- Never say "done" without production verification.
- Never initialize Supabase or read env vars at top 
  level. Always inside functions.
- useSession/useState/useEffect require 'use client'.
- Server components use getServerSession(authOptions).
- Frontend uses NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY.
- Backend uses SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY. Never mix.
- Every fix must include: what changed, build pass, 
  test pass, production verification.

## After Every Push
- Update SESSION_HISTORY.md with: date, commit hash, 
  files changed, what was verified, what remains unproven
- Update CURRENT_STATE.md section B (what is broken) 
  to remove anything you just fixed
- If a fix closes an AUTOMATION_BACKLOG.md item, mark 
  it DONE with the commit hash and date

These updates are part of the commit. Not separate.

## Locked Decisions (never change without asking)
- Pricing: Free forever + Pro $29/mo
- Tagline: "Finished work, every morning"
- No trial countdown. No credit card for free tier.
- Nicole Vreeland: never a reference or directive target
- Brandon is never the training mechanism

## Quality Standard
- If fixing a bug, scan the file for architectural flaws
- Fix the class not the instance
- Every commit must be verified against production
- "Build passed" is not verification
